{{Infobox philosopher | image = | region = Western Philosophy | era = [[20th-century philosophy]] | name = Delia Steinberg Guzm√°n | birth_date = January 7, 1943 | birth_place = [[Buenos Aires]], [[Argentina]] | death_date = | death_place = | school_tradition = [[Esotericism]], [[Theosophy (Blavatskian)|Theosophy]], [[Neoplatonism]], [[Humanism]] | influences = [[Plato]], [[Helena Blavatsky]], [[Jorge √Ångel Livraga Rizzi]] }}
'''Delia Steinberg Guzm√°n''', ([[Buenos Aires]], 1943), is a philosopher, musician and writer<ref>[http://www.editorial-na.com/tag/delia-steinberg-guzman/ Editorial Nueva Acr√≥polis: Delia Steinberg Guzm√°n], consulted on June 19, 2015</ref><ref>[http://ocio.elcorteingles.es/libros/autores/delia-steinberg-guzman El Corte Ingl√©s], consulted on June 19, 2015</ref><ref>[http://dialnet.unirioja.es/servlet/autor?Codigo=1620495 Foundation Dialnet, University of La Rioja (Spain)], consulted on June 19, 2015</ref> and, since 1991, International President of the [[International Organization New Acropolis]], a non profit association dedicated to the promotion of philosophy, culture and volunteering. She was born in Buenos Aires, [[Argentina]], on 7 January 1943, and obtained the Spanish nationality in 1975. She was awarded the Cross of Paris in Arts, Sciences and Literature by the [[Acad√©mie fran√ßaise]].{{quotation needed|date=January 2018}}
== Biography == '''Delia Steinberg''' studied music from an early age and, at the age of 17, graduated from the National Conservatory of Music in Buenos Aires as Teacher of [[Piano]] and [[Musical composition|Composition]]. She then continued her studies under the Argentine concert [[pianist]] [[Flora Nudelman]], and later with the Russian master Hubert Brandenburg. Nudelman herself had been a pupil of [[Jorge Lalewicz]], who had studied under [[Anatoly Lyadov]] and [[Nicolai Rimsky-Korsakov]].
She completed her studies with a master's degree in [[Philosophy]] from the [[University of Buenos Aires]], and took specialist courses in [[Archaeology]] and [[History]], exact sciences, journalism and advertising.
In 1972 she became the Director of [[New Acropolis]] in [[Spain]] and, since the death of its founder and first international director, [[Jorge Livraga]], in 1991, she has been the international president of the organization.
In 1982 she founded the '''New Acropolis International Piano Competition''', which has been held annually in [[Madrid]] (Spain),<ref>[http://www.concursopianodeliasteinberg.org/?p=49 Trump 32 ¬∫ International Contest of Piano Delia Steinberg 2013], consulted on June 19, 2015</ref> and in 2008 was renamed the [[International Competition of Piano Delia Steinberg|Delia Steinberg International Piano Competition]]. This competition has been a member of the Alink-Argerich Foundation (AAF), promoted by the Argentine pianist [[Martha Argerich]], since December 2007.<ref>[http://www.alink-argerich.org/acro-2011.htm Alink-Argerich Foundation (AAF): Delia Steinberg International Piano Competition] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120302083833/http://www.alink-argerich.org/acro-2011.htm |date=2012-03-02 }}</ref> The competition is recognised for attracting a large number of entries and for the technical and artistic level of its participants.<ref>[http://www.forumclasico.es/RITMOOnLine/MusicaViva/tabid/61/ID/399/XXX-Concurso-Internacional-de-Piano-Delia-Steinberg-Un-gran-nivel.aspx Classic Forum: " the XXXth International Contest of Piano Delia Steinberg: A great Level"], published in May, 2011, consulted on June 19, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.variaciones.es/ganador-del-concurso-internacional-de-piano-delia-steinberg/ Variaciones: "Christopher Falzone - winner of the International Contest of Piano Delia Steinberg "], published in June, 2011, consulted on June 19, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.forumclasico.es/RITMOOnLine/MusicaViva/tabid/61/ID/1430/XXXI-Concurso-Internacional-de-Piano-Delia-Steinberg-Un-gran-nivel.aspx Classic Forum: "the XXXIst International Contest of Piano Delia Steinberg: A great level"], published in May, 2012, consulted on June 19, 2015</ref><ref>[http://www.espaciovictoria.es/noticias/77-31o-concurso-internacional-de-piano-delia-steinberg-2012 Espacio Cultural Victoria: "31¬∫ International Contest of Piano Delia Steinberg 2012"] {{webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20130412134923/http://www.espaciovictoria.es/noticias/77-31o-concurso-internacional-de-piano-delia-steinberg-2012 |date=2013-04-12 }}, winners' relation and links to [[National Radio of Spain]], published in Madrid on May 3, 2012, consulted on June 19, 2015</ref> In 1988 she founded [[Tristan Music Institute]] to promote [[music]] internationally.
In 1974 she became the editor of the magazine "Cuadernos de Cultura" (Cultural Notebooks)<ref>Dep. Legal M-1276-1974, {{issn|0213-0394}}</ref> and from 2000 has edited the magazine "Esfinge" (Sphinx),<ref>Dep. Legal M-9589-2000, {{issn|1576-673X}}</ref> published in Madrid (Spain) with the sponsorship of [[New Acropolis]].
== Works == * Los juegos de Maya (Madrid, 1980)<ref>Ed. N.A., Castell√≥n, Dep. Legal CS-69-1995, 3¬™ edici√≥n, {{ISBN|84-85982-49-5}}</ref> * Hoy v√≠... (Madrid, 1983)<ref>Ed. N.A., {{ISBN|978-84-85982-07-3}}</ref> * Me dijeron que... (Madrid, 1984) * El H√©roe Cotidiano. Reflexiones de un Fil√≥sofo (Madrid, 1¬™ ed. mayo de 1996)<ref>Ed. N.A., Madrid, 2¬™ ed. febrero de 2002, Dep. Legal M-25113-2002, {{ISBN|84-85982-57-6}}</ref> * Peligros del racismo. Reflexiones acerca del problema del racismo y alternativas filos√≥ficas para erradicarlo (with several authors) (Madrid, 1997)<ref>Ed. N.A., Madrid, 1¬™ ed. noviembre de 1997, Dep. Legal M-43692-1997, {{ISBN|84-85982-60-6}}</ref> * Colecci√≥n: Perlas de Sabidur√≠a (Madrid, 1¬™ ed. enero de 2002) ** El Car√°cter seg√∫n los Astros<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-75-4}}</ref> ** La Vida despu√©s de la Muerte<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-76-2}}</ref> ** Las Edades Esot√©ricas del Hombre<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-78-9}}</ref> ** C√≥mo se plasman los Sue√±os<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-79-7}}</ref> ** El Alma de la Mujer<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-80-0}}</ref> ** Libertad, Inexorabilidad<ref>Dep. Legal M-4811-2002, {{ISBN|84-85982-81-9}}</ref> ** Recuerdos y reminiscencias<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-82-7}}</ref> ** Esoterismo Pr√°ctico<ref>{{ISBN|84-85982-83-5}}</ref> * Para conocerse mejor (Madrid, 2004)<ref>Ed. N.A., Madrid, 2004, Dep. Legal M-50265-2004, {{ISBN|84-96369-00-5}}</ref> * Filosof√≠a para vivir (Madrid, 2005)<ref>Ed. N.A., Madrid, 1¬™ edici√≥n, noviembre de 2005, Dep. Legal M-48749-2005, {{ISBN|84-96369-13-7}}</ref> * ¬øQu√© hacemos con el coraz√≥n y la mente? (Madrid, 2005)<ref>Ed. N.A., Madrid, 1¬™ ed. noviembre de 2005, Dep. Legal M-48746-2005, {{ISBN|84-96369-12-9}}</ref> * El ideal de los Templarios (2015)<ref>[http://noticias.nueva-acropolis.es/2015/presentacion-del-libro-ideal-los-templarios-nueva-acropolis-madrid/ Noticias Nueva Acr√≥polis: "Presentaci√≥n del libro "El ideal de los Templarios" en Nueva Acr√≥polis Madrid"], de 11 de junio de 2015, co