'''Otto Fl√ºgel''' (16 June 1842, [[L√ºtzen]] ‚Äì 9 July 1914, D√∂lau, [[Halle (Saale)|Halle]]) was a [[Germany|German]] [[philosopher]] and [[theologian]].
==Biography== He studied at [[Schulpforta]] and [[University of Halle|Halle]], and took up pastoral work. He was made editor of the ''Zeitschrift f√ºr exacte Philosophie im Sinne des Neueren Philosophischen Realismus'' (‚ÄúJournal for exact philosophy in the sense of the newer [[philosophical realism]]‚Äù), and in 1894 was one of the founders of ''Zeitschrift f√ºr Philosophie und P√§dagogik''. He was a supporter of [[Herbartian]] realism, as opposed to New-[[Kantian]] speculations, yet he believed in the necessity of a revelation.<ref name=Americana>{{Americana|wstitle=Fl√ºgel, Otto |inline=1}}</ref>
==Works== Among his works may be mentioned:<ref name=Americana/> * ''Die Spekulative Theologie der Gegenwart'' (‚ÄúSpeculative theology of the present‚Äù) * ''Das Ich und die sittliche Idee im Leben der V√∂lker'' (‚ÄúThe ego and the moral idea in the life of peoples,‚Äù 1892) * ''√úber die pers√∂nliche Unsterblichkeit'' (‚ÄúOn personal immortality,‚Äù 1902) * ''Monismus und Theologie'' (‚Äú[[Monism]] and theology,‚Äù 1908)
